    "119482154": {
      "title": "How do two moving clocks fall out of sync? a tale of trucks, threads, and twins",
      "abstract": "In special relativity, a pair of clocks synchronized in their own reference frame are not synchronized in another. How do two clocks, initially synchronized and at rest in the laboratory frame, fall out of sync as their speed relative to the lab gradually increases? The answer lies in general-relativistic time dilation. The path to the answer sheds light on the thread-between-spaceships paradox (also called the Bell spaceship paradox), on the twin paradox, and on the character of length contraction."
    }
  },
